import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cx', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['cx'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['cx'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude values in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='name', y='cx', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['cx'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Longitude: {data["cx"].max():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
